 into mixing bowl and mix <b>5 sec\/speed 5<b>."},{"content":"Add flour, baking powder and salt and mix <b>5 sec\/speed 5<b> until just combined. Transfer into a large bowl and set aside. Clean and dry mixing bowl."},{"content":" <strong>Insert butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Place egg whites into mixing bowl and whip <b>2 min\/speed 4<b> or until stiff peaks form. <strong>Remove butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Fold egg whites through reserved batter in two batches."},{"content":"Place a large non-stick frying pan over a medium-low heat. Place a little of the butter into frying pan and allow to melt. Place 3 x ⅓-cupfuls of batter into pan (cooking 3 pancakes at a time) and cook for approx. 3 minutes, or until just starting to set at edges. Turn pancakes and cook for a further 3-4 minutes, or until golden. Transfer onto a plate and cover to keep warm. Repeat with remaining batter (makes approx. 15 pancakes in total). Serve pancakes warm, topped with reserved dried fruit compote and yoghurt."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Pancake batter can be made in advance and stored in the refrigerator for up to 24 hours.","Compote can be made in advance and stored in the refrigerator for up to 2 weeks.","Omit steps 1 and 2, replacing compote with pure maple syrup, honey or fresh berries.","Please refer to the Gluten free flour mix recipe on this recipe chip.","To make your own Gluten free baking powder, please refer to the recipe on this recipe chip.","To make your own ricotta, visit the My-Thermomix Recipe Platform (www.my-thermomix.com.au) and register to receive your free Welcome collection of 10 Thermomix favourite recipes, including homemade ricotta."],"basicInfo":["easy","45m","1h 25m","5 portions"]}